
Linux:
    Run ./bootstrap
	Run make twice. (The first run will fail, the second should succeed)
	Run make install

Windows:
    Open the appropriate MSVC project in the build sub-folder.
    

Dependencies:
    Whid depends on warlib and wxwidgets

    Warlibs homepage is: http://warlib.jgaa.com
    WxWidgets homepage is: http://www.wxwidgets.org

GUI:
    The GUI is built with the commercial version of DialogBlocks.
    WHID can be compiled and modified without this
    application. Buf if you intend to do alot of changes on the
    GUI, DialogBlocks will simplyfy your work.
